  "prompt": "How can I Multiply White gaussian noise with mean 1 to an image in matlab?",
  "response": "Here's a Matlab script to multiply white Gaussian noise with mean 1 to an image:\n\n```matlab\n% Read the original image\noriginalImage = imread('your_image.jpg');\n\n% Convert image to double for noise multiplication\nimageDouble = im2double(originalImage);\n\n% Generate white Gaussian noise with mean 1\nnoiseStdDev = 0.1; % Adjust standard deviation as needed\nnoise = 1 + noiseStdDev * randn(size(imageDouble));\n\n% Multiply image with noise\nnoisyImage = imageDouble .* noise;\n\n% Clip values to valid image range\nnoisyImage = max(0, min(noisyImage, 1));\n\n% Display original and noisy images\nsubplot(1,2,1);\nimshow(originalImage);\ntitle('Original Image');\n\nsubplot(1,2,2);\nimshow(noisyImage);\ntitle('Noisy Image');\n```\n\nKey points:\n- `im2double()` converts image to double\n- `randn()` generates Gaussian noise\n- `1 +` ensures mean of noise is 1\n- `.* ` performs element-wise multiplication\n- `max/min` clips values to valid range [0,1]\n\nAdjust `noiseStdDev` to control noise intensity.",
